## 6. Formal Verification in Lean 4

To ensure software reliability, core physical invariants of the `rusty-SUNDIALS` architecture are mechanically specified in the Lean 4 theorem prover. We focus strictly on bounding AI behavior to prevent the corruption of PDE physics:

```lean
/- Verification of Divergence-Free Decoder Construction -/
import Mathlib.Analysis.VectorCalculus

namespace RustySundials.DFLSI

/-- The decoded magnetic field is strictly divergence-free by construction,
    preventing the generation of unphysical magnetic monopoles by the AI. -/
theorem decoder_divergence_free (z : Vector k ℝ) 
    (A_decoder : Vector k ℝ → (ℝ³ → ℝ³))
    (h_smooth : ContDiff ℝ 2 (A_decoder z)) :
    let B_phys := curl (A_decoder z)
    divergence B_phys = 0 := by
  exact divergence_curl_is_zero (A_decoder z) h_smooth

end RustySundials.DFLSI

```

